<![CDATA[<h1 style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="4" color="#3366ff"><a href="http://www.cloudmybiz.com/tip-of-the-week-never-lose-a-thing-with-tags-in-salesforce/">Tip of the Week – Never lose a thing with "Tags" in Salesforce</a></font></h1><div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font size="2" face="Arial, sans-serif">Have you ever searched for that one specific record, but couldn’t remember enough details to find it? Is keeping track of all the Leads and Contacts you saw at that trade show a hassle? Don’t you wish you could take all the reports, dashboards, and solutions you need and put them into one folder? Twitter lets you tag posts to make them easier to find later on, and so does Facebook, and even Chatter.</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font size="2" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><font size="2">With Tags in Salesforce, you can do the same thing! Simply enable Tags in your org and you’re ready to find all your related records, no matter what object, in just a couple clicks. Now, you’ll be able to add tags to all your records, and you’ll have a </font><font size="2">new dropdown on the sidebar where you can instantly search for all your Recent Tags. Happy tagging, and keep an eye out for our next <a href="http://www.cloudmybiz.com/category/tip-of-the-week/">Tip of the Week</a>!</font></font></div><div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">- Jared and the Salesforce Guys</font></div><div><font size="2" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font size="2" face="Arial, sans-serif">P.S.: Winter ’14 is out! Catch our four favorite features in next week’s blog post.</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div></div><div style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"